CLASS 3: ReconQueueScheduler.java
@Component with @EnableScheduling
Uses a dedicated TaskScheduler bean (NOT the default single-threaded one):

```java
@Bean
public TaskScheduler queueTaskScheduler() {
    ThreadPoolTaskScheduler scheduler = new ThreadPoolTaskScheduler();
    scheduler.setPoolSize(3);
    scheduler.setThreadNamePrefix("fobo-queue-scheduler-");
    scheduler.setWaitForTasksToCompleteOnShutdown(true);
    scheduler.setAwaitTerminationSeconds(60);
    return scheduler;
}
```

Three @Scheduled methods:

- completionPoller: fixedDelay = ${fobo.queue.poll.interval.ms:5000}
- timeoutDetector: fixedDelay = ${fobo.queue.timeout.check.interval.ms:60000}
